12:33.883 --> 12:35.383
wandering into frame and mucking it up.

12:35.384 --> 12:37.328
I am... I'm very sorry, Andy.

12:37.643 --> 12:39.710
- We were just trying to help.
- You want to help?

12:39.711 --> 12:41.546
Sit out of frame and shut the fuck up

12:41.547 --> 12:43.320
while I film these Mini Caesars.

12:43.874 --> 12:45.541
Again, so sorry.

12:45.542 --> 12:47.777
Look, why don't you guys go
back to your bloody chairs?

12:48.133 --> 12:49.134
"Bloody"?

12:49.335 --> 12:50.829
[SOFTLY] Thanks. I'm sorry.

12:53.471 --> 12:54.538
Hey.

12:55.140 --> 12:56.812
- What was the note?
- What?

12:57.348 --> 12:59.893
What was the fuckin' note
that was so fuckin' important

12:59.893 --> 13:01.613
that you had to interrupt my shot?

13:03.596 --> 13:06.031
[SOFT CHUCKLE] Uh, mayb...

13:06.032 --> 13:08.300
Uh, maybe it could be "friggin' football"?

13:08.325 --> 13:09.847
- [SOFT LAUGHING]
- What?

13:10.752 --> 13:11.893
[SOFT LAUGH]

13:11.893 --> 13:13.961
Instead of him saying just "a football,"

13:13.962 --> 13:15.394
he says, "a friggin' football."

13:15.395 --> 13:16.395
[BOTH LAUGHING SOFTLY]

13:16.396 --> 13:17.455
Are you fuckin' idiots?

13:18.464 --> 13:20.340
[SHOUTING] Does anyone
think that's funnier?

13:21.265 --> 13:22.462
Anybody?

13:23.660 --> 13:24.812
All right, then.

13:27.047 --> 13:28.394
Okay, look, guys,

13:28.395 --> 13:30.863
why don't you just get
out of here, all right?

13:31.045 --> 13:32.298
Yeah, that's all right, we'll...

13:32.299 --> 13:33.667
We'll go back to our chairs.

13:33.847 --> 13:35.940
No. I mean, get out of here.

13:36.079 --> 13:37.280
Leave.

13:39.039 --> 13:42.042
<i>[MOODY FUNK MUSIC]</i>

13:42.043 --> 13:44.143
<i>♪</i>

13:44.144 --> 13:45.311
How'd it go?

13:45.312 --> 13:46.480
I ran to the restroom,

13:46.481 --> 13:48.081
and I didn't see what just happened.

13:48.082 --> 13:49.082
I saw that you saw.

13:49.083 --> 13:50.316
Come on, let's get out of here.

13:50.317 --> 13:51.752
Oh, I love you, Sam.

13:51.753 --> 13:53.054
Thanks, but I don't need your help

13:53.055 --> 13:54.755
'cause I'm not humiliated.

13:55.769 --> 13:57.590
- <i>[UPBEAT LOUNGE MUSIC]</i>
- _

13:57.591 --> 13:59.119
What are we even doing here?

13:59.616 --> 14:01.217
That commercial got
nominated for a D Award.

14:01.219 --> 14:02.752
Let's just try to enjoy it.

14:02.753 --> 14:05.066
We had nothing to do with
it. We got kicked off the set.

14:05.391 --> 14:06.761
I choose to remember that

14:06.761 --> 14:08.362
we walked away with our heads held high.

14:08.363 --> 14:09.398
[DRUMROLL]

14:09.398 --> 14:11.466
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the stage</i>

14:11.467 --> 14:12.933
<i>Detroit's favorite son from</i>

14:12.934 --> 14:14.969
<i>your favorite television
show, "Martin."</i>

14:15.137 --> 14:17.672
<i>Please welcome Cole from "Martin."</i>

14:17.673 --> 14:20.674
[ENTHUSED CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

14:20.675 --> 14:23.577
[ORCHESTRAL MUSICAL FLOURISH]

14:23.578 --> 14:24.578
♪

14:24.579 --> 14:26.147
[CHEERING AND WHISTLING]

14:26.148 --> 14:28.183
Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh
ah-ah-ah!

14:28.451 --> 14:29.583
[CHEERING]

14:29.583 --> 14:30.721
What's up, Detroit?

14:30.721 --> 14:32.250
I'm Carl Anthony Payne II.

14:32.390 --> 14:33.624
Now, even though we actually

14:33.625 --> 14:35.393
never filmed "Martin" in Detroit,

14:35.394 --> 14:37.528
every time I would see all
those beautiful exterior shots,

14:37.529 --> 14:40.398
I would think, "Damn, such a nice place."

14:40.399 --> 14:43.595
[ENTHUSED CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

14:43.595 --> 14:45.802
All right, now, I know
you guys are thinking

14:45.803 --> 14:47.138
I came alone, right?

14:47.139 --> 14:50.573
I brought Carl Anthony Payne III!

14:50.574 --> 14:53.438
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

14:59.628 --> 15:01.572
Now, the producers of the show,

15:01.787 --> 15:03.754
they saw this bit and
asked me not to do it.

15:03.755 --> 15:05.690
They thought it wasn't
good. But I ask you guys.

15:05.691 --> 15:06.757
Is this good?

15:06.758 --> 15:08.426
[AS PUPPET] What's up, guys?

15:08.427 --> 15:11.562
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

15:11.563 --> 15:13.031
Ladies and gentlemen, welcome to

15:13.032 --> 15:15.434
Detroit's biggest night in advertising...

15:15.435 --> 15:17.668
[AS PUPPET] The D Awards!

15:17.669 --> 15:20.671
<i>[ORCHESTRAL FANFARE]</i>

15:20.672 --> 15:23.106
<i>♪</i>

15:23.107 --> 15:25.009
[HOOTING]

15:25.010 --> 15:27.379
[TAME APPLAUSE]

15:27.380 --> 15:28.827
Congratulations.

15:29.657 --> 15:31.604
All right, guys, it's time for the big one.

15:31.604 --> 15:34.316
The D Award for Consumer
TV 30-Second Single.

15:34.725 --> 15:35.992
Here's our first nominee.

15:35.993 --> 15:38.695
<i>[GENTLE ACOUSTIC GUITAR MUSIC]</i>

15:38.696 --> 15:39.697
<i>♪</i>

15:39.698 --> 15:41.198
<i>♪ Memories ♪</i>

15:41.199 --> 15:44.135
<i>♪ Hide between these bricks ♪</i>

15:44.136 --> 15:46.570
<i>♪</i>

15:46.571 --> 15:48.271
<i>♪ Picture frames ♪</i>

15:48.272 --> 15:52.275
<i>♪ Hold picture perfect moments ♪</i>

15:52.482 --> 15:53.909
They stole our pitch.

15:53.911 --> 15:55.213
Don't flatter yourself.

15:55.432 --> 15:57.232
A lot of people can have the same idea.

15:57.233 --> 16:00.301
<i>♪ Turn all our stories ♪</i>

16:00.302 --> 16:02.933
<i>♪ For love always
wherever we go ♪</i>

16:02.958 --> 16:04.622
_

16:05.575 --> 16:06.775
<i>♪</i>

16:06.776 --> 16:08.365
[APPLAUSE]

16:09.111 --> 16:11.146
Next up, Better Made Chips

16:11.147 --> 16:12.810
from Pomerantz and Klein.

16:12.810 --> 16:14.130
Let's get a drink.

16:14.130 --> 16:16.097
<i>♪ Memories hide
between these bricks ♪</i>

16:16.122 --> 16:17.130
See?

16:20.388 --> 16:24.025
[DISTANT] <i>♪ Picture frames
hold picture perfect... ♪</i>

16:24.026 --> 16:25.711
Can I have a Robert Palmer, please?

16:25.960 --> 16:27.531
- Hey.
- "Pizza, pizza."

16:27.989 --> 16:29.790
Can I whip this napkin
at the back of your head?

16:29.791 --> 16:31.585
Abso-fuckin'-lutely
not.

16:32.800 --> 16:34.207
There he is!

16:34.207 --> 16:35.574
Oh, for Christ sake...

16:35.575 --> 16:37.743
Funny seeing you in here again.

16:38.380 --> 16:40.583
Oh, I've seen that look before.

16:40.747 --> 16:43.316
You're getting ready to take a big dump.

16:43.595 --> 16:46.484
And in a minute, I'll
be wiping your little bun

16:46.486 --> 16:48.620
down with a wet towel

16:48.621 --> 16:50.697
and pouring baby powder on your tuchus,

16:50.722 --> 16:54.258
so your anus wouldn't
turn red as Rudolph's nose.

16:54.260 --> 16:56.521
Why were you always
changing my diaper, man?

16:56.697 --> 16:58.230
You're not even related to me.

16:58.231 --> 16:59.984
You should not have been doing that.

16:59.984 --> 17:01.840
Oh, jeez, kid.

17:02.351 --> 17:04.567
Your dad would bring you into work,

17:04.709 --> 17:06.910
and then he would get so
busy he wouldn't have time

17:06.911 --> 17:10.590
to take care of you, so I set
up a spot for you in my office,

17:11.016 --> 17:14.084
let you play with my old Matchbox cars,

17:14.085 --> 17:15.719
and while all that was going on,

17:15.720 --> 17:18.481
you'd take a lot of craps,
and I'd clean 'em up.

17:18.738 --> 17:21.569
Look, I didn't mean to embarrass you.

17:22.161 --> 17:23.372
Oh, my God.

17:24.666 --> 17:27.532
I'm... I'm so sorry, Paul. I had no idea.

17:29.756 --> 17:31.276
Thank you for taking care of me.

17:31.301 --> 17:32.818
Oh, yeah.

17:33.536 --> 17:36.953
I just feel like I had
a hand in raising you.

17:37.789 --> 17:41.158
Now, why don't you hop up
here for old time's sake?

17:41.487 --> 17:43.768
- Paul...
- Aw, I'm just joking.

17:43.768 --> 17:46.159
- Okay.
- I'm just proud of you.

17:47.007 --> 17:50.875
But I bet your dumps are way bigger

17:51.008 --> 17:52.692
and way messier.

17:53.344 --> 17:54.774
I'd love to see 'em,

17:55.727 --> 17:58.650
even if just in the toilet.

17:58.651 --> 18:00.122
Oh, damn it.

18:01.786 --> 18:03.323
Say it. "Pizza, pizza."

18:04.037 --> 18:05.060
Say it.

18:05.670 --> 18:06.903
Let's get out of here.

18:06.904 --> 18:08.471
Let's get our pea coats and go.

18:08.472 --> 18:09.779
Let's get our pea coats
and get out of here.

18:10.075 --> 18:12.464
<i>Mmm, delicious Little Caesars.</i>

18:12.844 --> 18:14.277
- <i>Pizza, pizza.</i>
- [LAUGHTER]

18:14.278 --> 18:15.813
<i>And there you have it.</i>

18:15.814 --> 18:18.681
<i>Even a football to the
head won't stop you</i>

18:18.682 --> 18:21.485
<i>from enjoying Little Caesars Pizza.</i>

18:21.486 --> 18:23.587
- Idiots.
- You're all sheep!

18:23.588 --> 18:25.552
Well, no surprises here, guys.

18:25.552 --> 18:29.154
The winner is: Little
Caesars, Cramblin Duvet.

18:29.155 --> 18:31.889
- Oh, my God!
- We did it!

18:31.890 --> 18:33.649
A fuckin' D Award!

18:33.649 --> 18:34.852
Aah!

18:34.852 --> 18:38.121
<i>[UPBEAT MOTOWN MUSIC]</i>

18:38.715 --> 18:42.285
<i>♪ You got me believing in you ♪</i>

18:42.286 --> 18:44.287
[LAUGHS INCREDULOUSLY]

18:44.288 --> 18:47.589
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

18:47.590 --> 18:51.227
[LAUGHS] Uh... ah.

18:51.561 --> 18:53.843
When... you know, when I was first

18:53.843 --> 18:55.441
hit in the head with a football,

18:55.979 --> 18:59.935
I-I thought, hmm, this
would be a great commercial,

19:00.450 --> 19:02.318
because it was funny, you know,

19:02.319 --> 19:04.067
and I always thought it was funny.

19:04.289 --> 19:07.034
Uh, and I was always in on the joke.

19:07.497 --> 19:09.105
So, to you I say...

19:09.592 --> 19:11.060
welcome to the joke!

19:11.061 --> 19:12.227
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

19:12.228 --> 19:13.692
[CHUCKLES] Tim.

19:16.078 --> 19:19.375
Commercials have the
power to change the world.

19:20.102 --> 19:22.505
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

19:22.506 --> 19:25.575
<i>♪ You got me
believing in you... ♪</i>

19:27.745 --> 19:29.946
It's weird. All I've ever wanted

19:29.947 --> 19:31.609
was to win a D Award.

19:32.215 --> 19:33.916
Doesn't feel like I thought it would.

19:34.118 --> 19:36.020
Yeah, that's 'cause we
didn't do anything to win it.

19:36.021 --> 19:39.146
That's right. This is meaningless.

19:39.689 --> 19:41.056
Hey, guys, congratulations.

19:41.057 --> 19:42.836
- Suck it, pal.
- We beat you, you lost,

19:42.861 --> 19:44.649
you're a piece of shit,
and nobody loves you.

19:44.794 --> 19:46.222
It's an empty victory.

19:46.396 --> 19:47.843
Yeah, sure is.

19:48.231 --> 19:49.765
Hey, fellas. Congratulations.

19:49.766 --> 19:50.766
- Oh.
- Yeah,

19:50.767 --> 19:51.899
it was a great commercial.

19:51.899 --> 19:53.734
Thank you so much, Carl, but honestly,

19:53.735 --> 19:55.669
we had nothing to do with it.

19:57.022 --> 19:59.406
Hmm. You know...

19:59.736 --> 20:01.337
this reminds me of the time

20:01.338 --> 20:03.238
"Martin" won the 1994 Image Award

20:03.239 --> 20:05.074
for Outstanding Comedy Series.

20:05.075 --> 20:06.441
- Oh, yeah, magical night.
- Yeah, of course.

20:06.442 --> 20:08.110
- I remember that.
- Yeah, yeah, it was great.

20:08.111 --> 20:09.776
Right? We won.

20:10.704 --> 20:14.573
You know, but it didn't feel like my award.

20:14.574 --> 20:16.175
Oh, yeah, 'cause you had to share it

20:16.176 --> 20:18.910
with Martin and Tommy and Pam and Gina

20:18.911 --> 20:20.260
and Sheneneh.

20:20.915 --> 20:22.741
Well, Sheneneh was Martin.

20:23.557 --> 20:25.283
But you know what, that's beside the point.

20:25.284 --> 20:27.052
I mean, you know, that
was just my ego talking.

20:27.053 --> 20:28.143
You know what I'm saying?

20:28.143 --> 20:30.546
I mean, since then I've learned
to appreciate the achievement.

20:30.546 --> 20:32.477
You know, you put it like
that, it's pretty cool.

20:32.726 --> 20:35.594
It's like the D Award is the Image Award,

20:35.595 --> 20:37.752
and we're "Martin." [LAUGHS SOFTLY]

20:37.811 --> 20:38.911
No.

20:39.813 --> 20:42.730
You're Cole... from "Martin."

20:43.579 --> 20:45.723
Well, that's... pretty cool, too.

20:46.248 --> 20:47.493
Oh, I know it is.

20:47.914 --> 20:49.153
Take it easy, fellas.

20:50.063 --> 20:52.292
- BOTH: Thanks, Carl.
- Appreciate it.

20:53.699 --> 20:56.226
- Wait, Martin was Sheneneh?
- I know!

20:56.226 --> 20:57.626
- What the hell?
- How?

20:57.628 --> 20:59.889
<i>I met the real Sheneneh once.</i>

20:59.914 --> 21:00.849
<i>Yeah.</i>

21:00.874 --> 21:02.085
God bless you.

21:03.438 --> 21:05.530
[STAMMERS] Thank you.

21:05.851 --> 21:06.952
[STIFLED LAUGHTER]

21:06.952 --> 21:09.284
And never... never...

21:09.285 --> 21:11.760
Let a teacher tell you that you're fat.

21:11.988 --> 21:14.825
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]
